AI-Powered Hair and Scalp Diagnosis System (AI-HSDS)
📋 OverviewThe AI-Powered Hair and Scalp Diagnosis System (AI-HSDS) is a deep learning-based diagnostic platform designed for rapid, objective, and personalized scalp health assessment. Developed by a team of B.Tech Artificial Intelligence students at Vidya Jyothi Institute of Technology, this system addresses the subjectivity and time constraints of traditional trichological examinations.
🚀 Key Features
Multi-Class Diagnosis: Automatically detects and classifies up to 14 distinct conditions, including Alopecia Areata, Seborrheic Dermatitis, Folliculitis, and Dandruff.
Vision Transformer (ViT) Core: Utilizes a sophisticated ViT architecture to capture both local textures and global spatial dependencies across microscopic scalp images.
Lifestyle Integration: Correlates diagnosed conditions with user-reported environmental factors (air quality, sun exposure) and stress levels.
Personalized Recommendations: Generates hyper-personalized treatment strategies, mapping diagnosed issues to specific nutritional advice and therapeutic solutions.
Data Security: Implements LSB-based Steganography to securely embed diagnostic results directly into scalp images for privacy-preserving data transmission.
🛠️ Technical Stack
Frameworks: TensorFlow 2.19.0, Keras 3.10.0
Architectures: Vision Transformer (ViT), 
MobileNetV2Preprocessing: OpenCV, PIL,
CLAHE (Contrast Limited Adaptive Histogram Equalization)
Interface: Gradio for real-time web-based deployment
Environment: Python 3.9+, NVIDIA CUDA for GPU acceleration
📊 System Architecture
The system follows a modular five-phase pipeline:
Data Acquisition: Loading high-resolution or dermoscopic images.
Preprocessing: Resizing (224x224), CLAHE enhancement, and normalization.
ViT Inference Engine: Patch partitioning and global self-attention processing.
Classification: MLP head and Softmax logic for probability scoring.
User Advisory: Interactive dashboard providing diagnosis and care insights.
📈 Results
Performance: Achieved high diagnostic accuracy (evaluated at >84% in conclusion) with a lightweight model size of approximately 10.2 MB.
Convergence: Demonstrated stable training and validation curves using the Adam optimizer and early stopping techniques.
Explainability: Utilizes attention-based visualizations to highlight specific scalp regions influencing the AI's prediction.
